        }
      ],
      "interface_notes": [
        {
          "stress_strain_distribution": "Uniform KAM distribution (~1.31°) near fracture surface in 1.3Al steel indicates homogeneous strain, contrasting with inhomogeneous strain in 0Al steel."
        },
        {
          "slippage_situation": "NiAl clusters enhance uniform plasticity and delay crack initiation; secondary cracks and void coalescence deflect the main crack."
        }
      ],
      "phase_evolution": "NiAl clusters and ε-carbides nucleate independently during tempering at 180°C; Ni and Al do not compete with C partitioning. A fraction of NiAl clusters nucleates on Si-enriched banded zones, providing additional heterogeneous nucleation sites."
    }
